{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8f08048a-82dc-4f27-aeb1-2ca4412f6ce4","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. Note that the `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so I'll assist directly.\n\nHere are your main options for analysis:\n\n### 1. `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n### 2. `lldb` with SOS (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`\n\n### 3. WinDbg (Windows)\nLoad the dump, then use `!analyze -v` and SOS commands.\n\n---\n\n**Quick start recommendation:** Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`, then type `pe` to print the exception and `clrstack` to see the stack trace. That usually reveals the root cause.\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and run the analysis on your file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27d48e6c-7ce2-4f9a-8e94-eea90057420e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":409,"requestId":"D807:260F1B:FC1DA8:1223A77:69F2B6AB"},"id":"41eb90f1-c16c-4769-b4bd-70a7f606793b","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:56:06.550Z","parentId":"880929ea-2842-4adc-9e85-9d5350bac7a0"}
